...tipped the driver 1 00 bucks
and walked away.

669
00:45:32,179 --> 00:45:33,373
Did you try his apartment?

670
00:45:33,547 --> 00:45:34,707
-He moved.
-I know.

671
00:45:34,882 --> 00:45:37,248
It's a loft. No doorman.
I rang, nobody answered.

672
00:45:37,418 --> 00:45:40,080
-I called, I got the machine.
-So he could be anywhere.

673
00:45:40,254 --> 00:45:43,246
Arthur downtown is not a good idea.
Some goddamn loft.

674
00:45:43,424 --> 00:45:46,154
-Where's his daughter?
-I don't know. Spain, lndia.

675
00:45:46,326 --> 00:45:49,454
Mars. She's crazier than he'll ever be.

676
00:45:49,630 --> 00:45:51,461
Barry's taking over on U/North.

677
00:45:51,632 --> 00:45:53,429
We got a lot of groveling to do.

678
00:45:53,600 --> 00:45:55,693
You didn't exactly charm Karen Crowder.

679
00:45:55,869 --> 00:45:57,097
I was punting.

680
00:45:57,271 --> 00:45:59,933
You gotta saddle up here
and get things under control.

681
00:46:00,107 --> 00:46:01,096
Saddle up?

682
00:46:01,275 --> 00:46:04,335
He needs to be under a doctor's care.
He needs to be admitted.

683
00:46:04,511 --> 00:46:06,843
-Where?
-Does that really matter?

684
00:46:07,014 --> 00:46:09,915
Michael, U/North needs to know
he's under control.

685
00:46:10,083 --> 00:46:13,450
He's in a facility. They've been shook up.
They need to be reassured.

686
00:46:13,620 --> 00:46:15,815
-It's not gonna be that easy.
-Why the hell not?

687
00:46:15,989 --> 00:46:19,789
Because the laws in New York are
pretty tough on involuntary commitment.

688
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:21,518
Did you see this fucking tape?

689
00:46:21,695 --> 00:46:24,391
I'm not arguing with you, Barry.
I'm telling you how it is.

690
00:46:24,565 --> 00:46:27,693
You know what, guys?
We got 600 lawyers in this place.

691
00:46:27,868 --> 00:46:31,360
Why don't we find out which one knows
about psychiatric-commitment statutes?

692
00:46:31,538 --> 00:46:34,200
I can tell you that right now. It's Arthur.

693
00:46:45,853 --> 00:46:47,878
<i>I'm at the door. We're good to go.</i>

694
00:46:49,056 --> 00:46:52,719
Yeah, roger that.
Let's keep a radio check every five, okay?

695
00:46:52,893 --> 00:46:55,054
Every five minutes, copy that.

696
00:47:31,164 --> 00:47:33,257
<i>Hello, you've reached Arthur's machine.</i>

697
00:47:33,433 --> 00:47:36,698
<i>If you wish to leave a message,</i>
<i>please do so after the tone.</i>

698
00:47:37,838 --> 00:47:40,102
<i>Arthur, pick up the phone.</i>

699
00:47:40,274 --> 00:47:44,677
<i>Arthur, pick up the phone</i>
<i>and talk to me.</i>

700
00:47:46,513 --> 00:47:49,482
<i>No? Not gonna do it?</i>

701
00:47:50,284 --> 00:47:53,378
What happened yesterday morning,
forget it. It doesn't matter.

702
00:47:53,554 --> 00:47:55,613
Someday you and I
are gonna laugh about it.

703
00:47:55,789 --> 00:47:57,256
But you gotta call me back.

704
00:47:57,424 --> 00:47:59,824
You gotta call me back soon, Arthur.

705
00:48:00,160 --> 00:48:02,094
<i>I'll tell you what.</i>

706
00:48:02,262 --> 00:48:05,254
<i>Because you said it yourself.</i>
<i>Part of this is definitely madness.</i>

707
00:48:05,432 --> 00:48:07,798
<i>And there's a chemical part.</i>
<i>We both know it.</i>

708
00:48:08,168 --> 00:48:10,193
<i>But if you're willing to start with that...</i>

709
00:48:10,370 --> 00:48:13,498
<i>...then I'm more than willing to</i>
<i>meet you halfway and say, yes...</i>

710
00:48:13,674 --> 00:48:17,132
...this situation sucks.
This case sucks. U/North sucks.

711
00:48:17,311 --> 00:48:19,905
We can start with that.
All right, Arthur? You hear me?

712
00:48:20,080 --> 00:48:21,741
You're right about what we are.

713
00:48:22,449 --> 00:48:25,885
<i>I'm saying you're crazy. I'm saying</i>
<i>that your behavior is out of control.</i>

714
00:48:26,053 --> 00:48:27,645
<i>But I'm telling you you're right.</i>

715
00:48:27,821 --> 00:48:31,279
You called it. We're janitors, I get it.

716
00:48:33,226 --> 00:48:35,160
But we came to this, Arthur.

717
00:48:36,096 --> 00:48:39,156
<i>We made decisions.</i>
<i>It didn't happen overnight.</i>

718
00:48:39,333 --> 00:48:43,429
You can't just suddenly stop and say,
"That's it, game over. I'm into miracles."

719
00:48:44,371 --> 00:48:46,168
<i>Arthur. Come on.</i>

720
00:48:47,808 --> 00:48:49,935
Goddamn it,
pick up the phone and talk to me.

721
00:48:50,110 --> 00:48:52,442
Because whatever else
you think is so important...

722
00:48:52,613 --> 00:48:55,343
...you better let me help you,
because I'm telling you...

723
00:48:55,515 --> 00:48:59,713
...janitor to janitor, I don't see
anybody else with a broom on the horizon.

724
00:48:59,886 --> 00:49:02,320
It's me, buddy. I'm the--

725
00:49:02,489 --> 00:49:06,482
<i>Mailbox is full.</i>
<i>Your message cannot be recorded.</i>

726
00:50:06,987 --> 00:50:09,455
-Hello?
<i>-Hello. Is Anna there?</i>

727
00:50:09,623 --> 00:50:10,988
Hang on.

728
00:50:14,394 --> 00:50:15,918
<i>Anna!</i>

729
00:50:17,931 --> 00:50:20,024
<i>Where is she? Anna!</i>

730
00:50:22,636 --> 00:50:24,331
<i>-Anna!</i>
<i>-Anna!</i>

731
00:50:25,305 --> 00:50:27,603
<i>Anna, you've got a phone call!</i>

732
00:50:30,243 --> 00:50:32,336
<i>Where is she? Anna!</i>

733
00:50:43,724 --> 00:50:44,816
Hello?

734
00:50:45,292 --> 00:50:47,419
Anna, hi. It's Arthur.

735
00:50:47,594 --> 00:50:50,154
<i>-Hey.</i>
-Did you get some sleep?

736
00:50:50,597 --> 00:50:52,155
<i>I guess.</i>

737
00:50:52,332 --> 00:50:54,300
<i>Did you think about what we said?</i>

738
00:50:54,468 --> 00:50:57,096
-Yeah.
<i>-You didn't tell anybody, did you?</i>

739
00:50:57,270 --> 00:51:01,798
No. My sister's spying on me,
but that's normal.

740
00:51:01,975 --> 00:51:04,671
Yeah. Because I meant what I said.

741
00:51:04,845 --> 00:51:07,245
<i>I know. I know. It's just...</i>

742
00:51:08,381 --> 00:51:12,181
...there's, like, 450 people in this lawsuit.

743
00:51:13,019 --> 00:51:15,146
Why are you choosing me?

744
00:51:16,456 --> 00:51:18,822
I don't know. I'm crazy, right?

745
00:51:18,992 --> 00:51:20,550
<i>That's for sure.</i>

746
00:51:20,727 --> 00:51:22,695
I mean, does it--?
Does it really matter?

747
00:51:22,863 --> 00:51:27,027
<i>I mean, isn't it what we wait for?</i>
<i>To meet someone? And they're--</i>

748
00:51:27,200 --> 00:51:28,497
<i>They're like a lens...</i>

749
00:51:28,668 --> 00:51:32,331
...and suddenly you're looking
through them and everything changes...

750
00:51:32,506 --> 00:51:34,497
...and nothing can ever be
the same again.

751
00:51:34,674 --> 00:51:36,335
<i>Who you talking to?</i>

752
00:51:36,510 --> 00:51:39,240
It's for me, okay? I get calls too.

753
00:51:39,412 --> 00:51:40,845
That guy?

754
00:51:41,014 --> 00:51:44,506
Same guy. Same guy.

755
00:51:45,152 --> 00:51:46,517
Sorry.

756
00:51:47,554 --> 00:51:51,854
No. That's-- That's okay.
My mother used to listen to my calls.

757
00:51:52,025 --> 00:51:54,721
<i>She can't believe I can do anything</i>
<i>on my own.</i>

758
00:51:54,895 --> 00:51:56,362
Well, that'll change.

759
00:51:57,097 --> 00:51:58,394
<i>I guess.</i>

760
00:51:58,565 --> 00:52:01,591
<i>Yeah, but, see,</i>
<i>that's something we can show her.</i>

761
00:52:01,768 --> 00:52:04,896
<i>That you can do something.</i>

762
00:52:05,071 --> 00:52:08,199
<i>That we could-- We could do that together</i>
<i>if you want. I mean....</i>

763
00:52:08,375 --> 00:52:10,639
<i>I mean that I can help you do that.</i>

764
00:52:11,578 --> 00:52:14,206
I can get you 1 2 by Monday.

765
00:52:14,381 --> 00:52:16,440
Twelve's weak. Twelve looks bad.

766
00:52:16,616 --> 00:52:18,083
How do you figure that?

767
00:52:18,251 --> 00:52:21,812
They look at 75 and they look at you
and they wonder what the problem is.

768
00:52:21,988 --> 00:52:24,081
You say 1 2.
That's gonna make people nervous.

769
00:52:24,257 --> 00:52:27,192
This was the day before yesterday.
Let me get my ducks in order.

770
00:52:27,360 --> 00:52:28,588
What's the car worth?

771
00:52:28,762 --> 00:52:30,957
It's a lease. It's the firm's.

772
00:52:31,131 --> 00:52:35,033
So? You go to the bank.
You've got the apartment. You refinance.

773
00:52:35,202 --> 00:52:37,830
I can't. I did that three months ago.

774
00:52:38,772 --> 00:52:40,467
Are you back at the tables?

775
00:52:40,640 --> 00:52:43,575
Like I need that kind of action.
I don't have enough going on.

776
00:52:46,746 --> 00:52:48,771
I hope you're kidding.

777
00:52:48,949 --> 00:52:53,010
If he finds out you're playing cards with
his money, there's no dialogue after that.

778
00:52:54,621 --> 00:52:56,612
Do everyone a favor.

779
00:52:56,823 --> 00:53:01,226
Get out the treasure map
and start digging.

780
00:53:01,995 --> 00:53:03,485
You got a week.

781
00:53:04,831 --> 00:53:07,629
-Hey, Michael. How are you?
-Hi, Cindy. I'm good.

782
00:53:07,801 --> 00:53:11,100
Come in. He's been on the phone
all morning. What else is new?

783
00:53:11,271 --> 00:53:13,296
I am trying to get him out
in 1 5 minutes.

784
00:53:13,473 --> 00:53:15,907
-Is he upstairs?
-He's taken over the living room.

785
00:53:16,076 --> 00:53:17,976
What are you guys doing?
Get down here.

786
00:53:18,144 --> 00:53:22,911
Soroyo, I told you to keep an eye on
these kids, make sure they're downstairs.

787
00:53:37,430 --> 00:53:38,920
Marty?

788
00:53:41,167 --> 00:53:44,034
You know what he's doing?
He's making their case.

789
00:53:44,704 --> 00:53:47,571
I'm going through his files here,
I'm reading this...

790
00:53:47,741 --> 00:53:49,606
...he's building a case against U/North.

791
00:53:49,776 --> 00:53:51,767
-Nobody's gonna let him do that.
-Let him?

792
00:53:51,945 --> 00:53:53,344
Who the hell's gonna stop him?

793
00:53:53,880 --> 00:53:56,542
You know what I just heard?
He's calling these plaintiffs.

794
00:53:56,716 --> 00:54:00,914
This woman from the deposition,
he's calling these people now.

795
00:54:01,087 --> 00:54:04,022
He's got these discovery documents.
This is a fucking nightmare.

796
00:54:04,190 --> 00:54:07,751
I tried him. Can't even leave a message.
He's got the machine jammed up.

797
00:54:07,928 --> 00:54:10,453
-Is that his briefcase?
-Yeah.

798
00:54:11,031 --> 00:54:12,828
-Why?
-We've been looking for it.

799
00:54:12,999 --> 00:54:16,526
I don't know. It came up here
with all the other stuff from his office.

800
00:54:16,703 --> 00:54:20,434
You can't believe
the crap he's got in here.

801
00:54:21,474 --> 00:54:22,498
Listen, Marty...

802
00:54:24,477 --> 00:54:26,809
...I'm in a bind here.

803
00:54:27,981 --> 00:54:30,711
I need a loan. I need 80 grand.

804
00:54:31,885 --> 00:54:34,217
-I thought you were done with that.
-It's not that.

805
00:54:34,387 --> 00:54:37,220
It's not the cards. It's none of that.
It's the restaurant.

806
00:54:37,390 --> 00:54:38,982
Eighty thousand.

807
00:54:39,159 --> 00:54:40,626
I'm sorry to jump you like this.

808
00:54:40,794 --> 00:54:43,558
I've been trying to get a meeting
with you for two weeks.

809
00:54:44,331 --> 00:54:47,630
And I know about the merger,
whether I'm supposed to or not.

810
00:54:48,034 --> 00:54:49,729
There's nothing final on the merger.

811
00:54:49,903 --> 00:54:52,838
Well, that's why I'm asking you now.
You're my meal ticket.

812
00:54:53,006 --> 00:54:55,668
Once you're out,
it's me and Barry with strangers...

813
00:54:55,842 --> 00:54:57,742
...and I'm trying to explain what I do.

814
00:54:57,911 --> 00:55:00,971
Everybody knows how valuable you are.
Everybody who needs to know.

815
00:55:01,147 --> 00:55:02,808
I'm 45 years old and I'm broke.

816
00:55:02,983 --> 00:55:05,679
I've been riding shotgun for 1 2 years
and I got no equity.

817
00:55:05,852 --> 00:55:07,444
I'm sorry, I don't feel reassured.

818
00:55:07,620 --> 00:55:09,645
Nobody told you to
go into the bar business.

819
00:55:09,823 --> 00:55:12,383
I only opened it so I'd have
something else, a way out.

820
00:55:12,559 --> 00:55:14,220
I had no idea you were so unhappy.

821
00:55:14,394 --> 00:55:17,420
How many times did I ask you
to put me back on a litigation team?

822
00:55:17,597 --> 00:55:19,258
-How many?
-Anybody can go to court.

823
00:55:19,432 --> 00:55:20,660
You think that's special?

824
00:55:20,834 --> 00:55:23,496
-I was good at it.
-Wonderful. So are a lot of people.

825
00:55:23,970 --> 00:55:27,337
At this, what you do, you're great.

826
00:55:27,507 --> 00:55:31,773
For chrissakes, you got something
everybody wants. You have a niche.

827
00:55:31,945 --> 00:55:34,937
You made a place.
You made a niche for yourself.

828
00:55:35,115 --> 00:55:39,176
And if it's nostalgia-- "You should've seen
me when I was a DA back in Queens."

829
00:55:39,352 --> 00:55:42,753
--let me give you a serious piece of advice:
Leave it there.

830
00:55:42,922 --> 00:55:46,915
God forbid you're not as good as
you remember. I've seen that happen too.

831
00:55:47,794 --> 00:55:50,319
But I didn't come here for advice, did I?

832
00:55:50,897 --> 00:55:54,196
So this is what? I give you the loan
or you don't help out with Arthur?

833
00:55:54,367 --> 00:55:55,959
-I never said that.
-No?

834
00:55:56,136 --> 00:55:57,467
Maybe you should have.

835
00:55:57,637 --> 00:56:02,301
I don't know how you're gonna take care
of this, but this, this is cancer.

836
00:56:02,475 --> 00:56:05,638
This is something, we don't get it
reined in and cleaned up soon...

837
00:56:05,812 --> 00:56:07,939
...everything's vulnerable. Everything.

838
00:56:08,748 --> 00:56:12,081
-What are you telling me?
-That I'm counting on you.

839
00:56:12,452 --> 00:56:16,411
I'm telling you that by this time next week,
Arthur will be under control...

840
00:56:16,589 --> 00:56:20,150
...and everybody who needs to will have
been reminded of your infinite value.

841
00:56:20,326 --> 00:56:21,623
Jesus, Marty.

842
00:56:21,895 --> 00:56:23,294
Hey.

843
00:56:23,463 --> 00:56:25,488
When did you get so fucking delicate?

844
00:56:26,599 --> 00:56:28,157
I'm late.

845
00:57:07,807 --> 00:57:10,867
Why don't you just call Uncle Gene
and get the cops to help you?

846
00:57:11,044 --> 00:57:13,069
It's not that kind of a problem.

847
00:57:14,714 --> 00:57:17,114
-How much longer are we doing this?
-I don't know.

848
00:57:29,129 --> 00:57:32,929
If he comes back to get his car,
you call that number and let me know.

849
00:57:33,099 --> 00:57:36,227
-Thank you very much. I appreciate it.
-Okay. You're welcome.

850
00:57:43,610 --> 00:57:46,602
If we're not gonna get to the movie,
why don't you just say so?

851
00:57:46,779 --> 00:57:49,543
-What?
-I wanna go home.

852
00:57:49,716 --> 00:57:51,513
Come on, Henry.

853
00:57:54,921 --> 00:57:55,910
Hold up!

854
00:57:58,958 --> 00:58:00,823
Stay in the car. Lock the door.

855
00:58:02,462 --> 00:58:05,431
Arthur! Arthur!

856
00:58:05,598 --> 00:58:06,929
Wait up.

857
00:58:07,767 --> 00:58:11,168
Michael. Jeez. You scared me.

858
00:58:12,572 --> 00:58:15,302
-Making a delivery?
-No, no, no.

859
00:58:16,142 --> 00:58:18,770
Very funny. No, nothing like that.

860
00:58:18,945 --> 00:58:22,540
Here, take one, please. Really.
It's-- It's still warm.

861
00:58:22,715 --> 00:58:24,342
It's the best bread I ever tasted.

862
00:58:28,388 --> 00:58:30,117
So welcome home.

863
00:58:31,291 --> 00:58:34,226
I know, the hotel. I'm sorry.

864
00:58:34,394 --> 00:58:36,760
I was beginning to feel
a little overwhelmed.

865
00:58:36,930 --> 00:58:38,761
-But you're feeling better now?
-Yeah.

866
00:58:38,932 --> 00:58:41,423
-Much better, definitely.
-Not enough to call me back.

867
00:58:41,601 --> 00:58:44,832
Well, I was trying
to gather my thoughts...

868
00:58:45,004 --> 00:58:48,599
...before I called you,
and that's what I was doing.

869
00:58:49,242 --> 00:58:50,641
And how's that going?

870
00:58:50,810 --> 00:58:53,278
Yes, it's good, very good. I just....

871
00:58:53,580 --> 00:58:58,984
Well, I just need to make my thoughts
a little bit more precise. That's....

872
00:58:59,152 --> 00:59:00,449
That's my goal.

873
00:59:00,620 --> 00:59:03,987
As good as this feels,
you know where it goes.

874
00:59:04,157 --> 00:59:05,556
No. No. You're wrong.

875
00:59:05,725 --> 00:59:08,819
What makes this feel good
is that I don't know where it goes.

876
00:59:09,996 --> 00:59:13,159
How do I talk to you, Arthur?
So you hear me?

877
00:59:13,333 --> 00:59:17,861
Like a child? Like a nut?
Like everything's fine?

878
00:59:18,037 --> 00:59:21,803
What's the secret?
Because I need you to hear me.

879
00:59:21,975 --> 00:59:24,739
-Well, I hear everything.
-Then hear this.

880
00:59:25,178 --> 00:59:29,137
You need help.
Before this goes too far, you need help.

881
00:59:29,315 --> 00:59:30,543
You got great cards here.

882
00:59:30,717 --> 00:59:34,050
If you keep your clothes on, you can
do any goddamn thing you want.

883
00:59:34,220 --> 00:59:37,451
You want out, you're out.
You wanna bake bread, go with God.

884
00:59:37,624 --> 00:59:40,320
There's only one wrong answer
in this whole goddamn pile...

885
00:59:40,493 --> 00:59:42,256
...and you've got
your arms around it.

886
00:59:42,428 --> 00:59:45,727
-Well, I said I was sorry.
-You thought the hotel was overwhelming?

887
00:59:45,898 --> 00:59:48,458
You piss on this case,
they'll cut you off at the knees.

888
00:59:48,635 --> 00:59:51,900
-I don't know what you're talking about.
-I'm covering for you.

889
00:59:52,071 --> 00:59:55,563
I'm telling them everything's fine.
You're fine. Everybody's cool.

890
00:59:55,742 --> 00:59:58,973
I'm out running this "price of genius" story
to anybody who'll listen.

891
00:59:59,145 --> 01:00:03,377
And then I wake up this morning and I hear
you're calling this girl from Wisconsin...

892
01:00:03,549 --> 01:00:05,414
...messing with documents
and whatever else.

893
01:00:05,585 --> 01:00:08,110
-How can you know that?
