and then leave her at the airport?

1168
01:20:59,903 --> 01:21:01,495
<i>This is not a complicated person.</i>

1169
01:21:01,671 --> 01:21:04,504
<i>This is a girl who's never been</i>
<i>farther than Milwaukee.</i>

1170
01:21:04,674 --> 01:21:06,665
-Wait a minute. Now, wait.
<i>-No, you wait.</i>

1171
01:21:06,843 --> 01:21:11,075
She's coming home tomorrow
and when she does, if you call here again--

1172
01:21:11,247 --> 01:21:13,545
Are you telling me she's
in New York right now?

1173
01:21:14,017 --> 01:21:16,008
<i>This is a young girl, do you hear me?</i>

1174
01:21:16,185 --> 01:21:18,619
She's in the city right now?

1175
01:21:18,788 --> 01:21:20,346
<i>What kind of people are you?</i>

1176
01:21:20,523 --> 01:21:23,549
Listen. You just stay on the phone
one second. One second.

1177
01:21:56,259 --> 01:21:57,487
<i>Anna.</i>

1178
01:21:59,896 --> 01:22:01,386
Anna?

1179
01:22:02,198 --> 01:22:05,167
My name's Michael Clayton.
I'm a friend of Arthur's.

1180
01:22:05,335 --> 01:22:07,997
I spoke with your sister.
She told me you were here.

1181
01:22:09,305 --> 01:22:11,170
Please open the door, Anna.

1182
01:22:22,485 --> 01:22:24,180
What are you thinking?

1183
01:22:24,988 --> 01:22:30,290
I don't know. I'll watch the door.
You check his car. Let's get some details.

1184
01:22:33,129 --> 01:22:36,394
He didn't want to say
exactly what it was.

1185
01:22:38,267 --> 01:22:42,101
Just that when I got here,
he would pick me up...

1186
01:22:42,271 --> 01:22:44,637
...and show me, and I would see...

1187
01:22:45,608 --> 01:22:48,475
...that it was something
that would win the whole case.

1188
01:22:51,681 --> 01:22:53,546
Even this morning...

1189
01:22:53,716 --> 01:22:55,308
...I mean, I thought:

1190
01:22:56,853 --> 01:23:01,517
"Okay, if I get to the airport
and the ticket's not there, then I'll know.

1191
01:23:01,691 --> 01:23:06,788
Okay, you're stupid,
and you can go home now."

1192
01:23:09,399 --> 01:23:14,234
But it was there and he paid,
like, 800 dollars...

1193
01:23:14,404 --> 01:23:17,066
...for a first-class ticket.

1194
01:23:17,240 --> 01:23:18,707
And I just....

1195
01:23:22,645 --> 01:23:24,579
I got on the plane.

1196
01:23:27,350 --> 01:23:29,284
I believed him.

1197
01:23:34,057 --> 01:23:38,721
You think maybe he was
in some way disappointed?

1198
01:23:39,562 --> 01:23:43,555
Let's say that he knew that you
told somebody else about all of this...

1199
01:23:43,733 --> 01:23:47,169
...and, I don't know, in some crazy way,
he was disappointed by that?

1200
01:23:48,271 --> 01:23:51,172
-But I didn't.
-You must have told somebody else.

1201
01:23:51,340 --> 01:23:52,898
No.

1202
01:23:54,077 --> 01:23:56,238
He made me promise.

1203
01:23:57,747 --> 01:24:02,116
You didn't tell anybody else about this?
Not one other person?

1204
01:24:03,252 --> 01:24:04,651
No.

1205
01:24:09,425 --> 01:24:12,360
He really was crazy, wasn't he?

1206
01:24:25,108 --> 01:24:27,975
-You talking about this?
-Let me see.

1207
01:24:29,479 --> 01:24:31,140
-You know what that is?
-Yeah.

1208
01:24:32,081 --> 01:24:35,141
You said a favor.
That's more than a favor.

1209
01:24:35,318 --> 01:24:37,479
Well, nobody's gonna know
where it came from.

1210
01:24:38,855 --> 01:24:41,289
-Are you that jammed up?
-What are you talking about?

1211
01:24:41,457 --> 01:24:44,085
Who asked for this?
It's the restaurant, right?

1212
01:24:44,260 --> 01:24:46,751
One of these guys you owe?
"Get me a seal."

1213
01:24:46,929 --> 01:24:48,556
You really wanna know?

1214
01:26:05,875 --> 01:26:08,105
This just gets better and better.

1215
01:26:09,745 --> 01:26:11,337
What are we doing?

1216
01:28:13,002 --> 01:28:14,026
Freeze!

1217
01:28:14,203 --> 01:28:16,933
Right there, asshole! Don't move!

1218
01:28:17,106 --> 01:28:19,370
-It's all right, I'm a friend!
-Get your hands up!

1219
01:28:19,542 --> 01:28:22,067
Get your hands up now! Now!

1220
01:28:22,244 --> 01:28:24,178
-What's in your hand?
-It's a book.

1221
01:28:24,347 --> 01:28:27,214
Drop it! Drop it, now! Drop it!

1222
01:28:27,383 --> 01:28:30,682
-Turn around. Slowly.
-All right. All right. Okay.

1223
01:28:30,853 --> 01:28:32,684
-Who else is here?
-Nobody.

1224
01:28:32,855 --> 01:28:35,289
-I said, who else is here?
-Nobody's here!

1225
01:28:35,458 --> 01:28:36,857
Check in there.

1226
01:28:37,660 --> 01:28:40,959
You move, I'll take your head off.

1227
01:29:10,826 --> 01:29:15,263
Now I owe this scumbag and his wife--
Who's a complete piece of shit in my unit.

1228
01:29:15,431 --> 01:29:17,524
-Now I owe them both my balls.
-I'm sorry.

1229
01:29:17,700 --> 01:29:19,691
-You know I am.
-"Nobody will know it's me."

1230
01:29:19,869 --> 01:29:22,929
You know what happens they don't
bury this, that I gave you this?

1231
01:29:23,105 --> 01:29:24,470
It's bad. I know it.

1232
01:29:24,640 --> 01:29:27,700
I'm 1 8 months away from my 20.
You just put my pension in jeopardy.

1233
01:29:27,877 --> 01:29:29,845
-You made your point.
-It's not a point!

1234
01:29:30,012 --> 01:29:32,378
-Who called 91 1 ?
-What?

1235
01:29:32,681 --> 01:29:35,616
The building was empty. I was quiet.
I wasn't there very long.

1236
01:29:35,785 --> 01:29:38,219
Who called it in?
Does that make sense to you--?

1237
01:29:38,387 --> 01:29:39,945
This never happened.

1238
01:29:41,257 --> 01:29:43,282
You got these cops thinking
you're a lawyer.

1239
01:29:43,459 --> 01:29:45,518
You got these lawyers thinking
you're a cop.

1240
01:29:45,694 --> 01:29:49,824
You got everybody fooled, don't you?
Everybody but you.

1241
01:29:49,999 --> 01:29:52,092
You know exactly what you are.

1242
01:30:05,714 --> 01:30:07,238
We tried calling you six times.

1243
01:30:07,416 --> 01:30:09,543
But your machine must be
busted or something.

1244
01:30:11,387 --> 01:30:12,877
We gave it our best shot.

1245
01:30:14,223 --> 01:30:16,714
We ran out of red covers.
We only had 2000 in stock...

1246
01:30:16,892 --> 01:30:18,757
...so we did the other thousand in blue.

1247
01:30:40,182 --> 01:30:41,672
Is everything all right?

1248
01:30:41,851 --> 01:30:43,079
It's fine, yeah.

1249
01:30:43,786 --> 01:30:46,846
You have a van or something?
Because I have 25 boxes back there--

1250
01:30:47,022 --> 01:30:50,082
Do me a favor. Hang on to them.

1251
01:30:50,259 --> 01:30:52,489
I'll come back and pick everything up
next week.

1252
01:30:52,661 --> 01:30:54,720
-Seriously? Thanks, man.
-Yeah.

1253
01:31:15,284 --> 01:31:16,649
Hello.

1254
01:31:21,724 --> 01:31:25,023
Don. You go ahead. I'll catch up to you.

1255
01:31:25,594 --> 01:31:26,891
What?

1256
01:31:34,303 --> 01:31:36,464
<i>Do you know Michael Clayton?</i>

1257
01:31:36,639 --> 01:31:38,129
<i>Yeah, why?</i>

1258
01:31:38,307 --> 01:31:40,070
We have a situation.

1259
01:31:59,862 --> 01:32:01,420
Hey, did they find you?

1260
01:32:01,597 --> 01:32:04,623
-Who?
-Marty. I don't think they've gone in yet.

1261
01:32:12,808 --> 01:32:14,139
Marty.

1262
01:32:14,476 --> 01:32:17,673
Your phone's off. There's too much
going on for your phone to be off.

1263
01:32:17,846 --> 01:32:19,837
-I need a minute.
-Yeah, well, we're late--

1264
01:32:20,015 --> 01:32:21,642
We never got to finish last night.

1265
01:32:21,817 --> 01:32:23,944
Did you close the place?
You look like hell.

1266
01:32:24,119 --> 01:32:27,179
-No, I left right after you left.
-If you say so.

1267
01:32:27,356 --> 01:32:30,052
We've been here all night.
We had to make an announcement.

1268
01:32:30,225 --> 01:32:33,490
Jean! I need the thing, the envelope.

1269
01:32:33,662 --> 01:32:36,859
I wanted your input. I couldn't get you.
I had to pull the trigger.

1270
01:32:37,032 --> 01:32:39,967
I put Bob Nast and Kim,
probably a mistake.

1271
01:32:40,135 --> 01:32:43,468
They're gonna pull together a memorial
service by the end of the week.

1272
01:32:43,639 --> 01:32:45,903
I told them to call you
if they need any help.

1273
01:32:46,408 --> 01:32:49,172
No, no, no.
The other one. The other one.

1274
01:32:49,745 --> 01:32:52,043
So we cut you a check this morning.

1275
01:32:52,214 --> 01:32:55,513
There's some strings attached.
And Barry....

1276
01:32:55,684 --> 01:32:59,814
There's no way around this,
Barry's gonna have to be involved.

1277
01:33:03,592 --> 01:33:06,026
What if Arthur was on to something?

1278
01:33:06,195 --> 01:33:07,856
What do you mean? On to what?

1279
01:33:08,030 --> 01:33:10,897
U/North. What if he wasn't crazy?
What if he was right?

1280
01:33:11,066 --> 01:33:13,227
Right about what?
That we're on the wrong side?

1281
01:33:13,402 --> 01:33:15,836
Wrong side, wrong way,
everything, all of it.

1282
01:33:16,005 --> 01:33:18,940
This is news?
This case reeked from day one.

1283
01:33:19,108 --> 01:33:21,099
I gotta tell you how we pay the rent?

1284
01:33:21,276 --> 01:33:24,006
What would they do?
What would they do if he went public?

1285
01:33:24,179 --> 01:33:27,580
What would they do? Are you fucking soft?
They're doing it.

1286
01:33:27,750 --> 01:33:30,184
We don't straighten the settlement out
in 24 hours...

1287
01:33:30,352 --> 01:33:32,411
...they're gonna withhold
$9 million in fees.

1288
01:33:32,588 --> 01:33:35,557
Then they'll pull out the video of
Arthur doing his flashdance.

1289
01:33:35,724 --> 01:33:37,453
They'll sue us for legal malpractice.

1290
01:33:37,626 --> 01:33:41,289
Except there won't be anything to win
because the London merger will be dead...

1291
01:33:41,463 --> 01:33:44,125
...and we'll be selling off
the goddamn furniture.

1292
01:33:44,600 --> 01:33:46,295
That's 80.

1293
01:33:46,802 --> 01:33:48,599
We're calling it a bonus.

1294
01:33:49,438 --> 01:33:51,463
Three-year contract
at your current numbers.

1295
01:33:51,640 --> 01:33:53,267
That's assuming this all works out.

1296
01:33:53,442 --> 01:33:54,602
You're doing this now?

1297
01:33:56,278 --> 01:33:59,611
Look, I agreed to this, okay?
But there's rules now.

1298
01:33:59,782 --> 01:34:02,649
You want the contract,
you sign a confidentiality agreement.

1299
01:34:02,818 --> 01:34:04,911
It's gonna be bulletproof
and retroactive.

1300
01:34:05,087 --> 01:34:06,816
Because Marty's too nice to say it...

1301
01:34:06,989 --> 01:34:10,789
...but with all you know about this place,
the clients and people who work here...

1302
01:34:10,959 --> 01:34:13,519
...it makes it a little weird
when you ask for 80 grand.

1303
01:34:14,196 --> 01:34:16,892
If I was gonna shake anybody down,
I'd come to you...

1304
01:34:17,066 --> 01:34:19,728
